Amazon Business, rooted in the retail sector, is where we are reshaping how businesses buy and sell supplies. We provide a procurement solution to more than 5 million businesses across geographies and industries to help streamline their purchasing. What makes Amazon Business unique is that we also enable hundreds of thousands of third-party sellers to sell to business customers of all sizes, including public sector entities and multinational enterprises. Since launching in the U.S. in 2015, we have expanded to eight additional countries and reached $25 billion in worldwide annualized sales, more than half of which are from third-party sellers.
 
Across Amazon, we're working on technology that will transform purchasing and bring savings and efficiency for a digital, intelligent, and sustainable future. Through artificial intelligence, machine learning, and predictive analytics, Amazon Business (AB) brings automation and insights to provide a procurement solution to enable pioneering leaders to have a strategic role in transforming their organizations.
 
We are looking for a Sr Event Technology Manager with exceptional virtual, technical, and project management skills to support the development of planning processes, integration and implementation of event technology for the global AB marketing team. This is an opportunity for a dynamic, driven project manager to join our growing team and make a significant contribution building virtual events that enable our worldwide marketing strategies. To be successful in this role you will need to be creative, technically savvy, and driven to deliver high-quality customer-facing events. You should be dedicated to continually testing, measuring, and evolving event technology.
 
 Your responsibilities will include: 
 
 Onboarding, integration, and execution of a broad event technology portfolio 
 Work cross-functionally with event teams to identify, scale, produce, and execute event technology solutions 
 Management and technical implementation of virtual event hosting platforms and solutions used by event teams 
 Event live stream technical management 
 Partner with event marketers to define metrics, developing registration and onsite management/reporting that gathers metrics from conception to reconciliation (including viewership data for virtual events, data flow integrations, and others as needed) 
 Design/develop event microsite and registration platform templates, including but not limited to onsite check-in and mobile solutions 
 Work with program managers, business leaders, sales, internal/external tech teams, and key vendors to drive critical event technology initiatives related to virtual programs and content hosting 
 Event scheduling and prioritization (within the virtual platform and across the event team) 
 Researching, evaluating, and recommending new technologies and technology vendors to support event needs 
